{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Bilbrough Falls | photo = Goomoolahra.jpg | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = Bilbrough Falls | map = Queensland | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|28|13|22|S|153|17|06|E|type:waterbody_region:AU-QLD_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref name=gaz>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Bilbrough Falls|feature=QLD2564}}</ref><ref name=dnrm>{{cite QPN|2564|Bilbrough Falls|accessdate=22 May 2014}}</ref> | location = [[South East Queensland]], Australia | type = [[Waterfall#Types|Cascade]] | elevation = | height = | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Bilbrough Falls''', also known as the Goomoolahra Falls,<ref name=dnrm/> is a [[Waterfall#Types|cascade waterfall]] that is located within the [[Springbrook National Park]] in the [[South East Queensland|South East]] region of [[Queensland]], Australia.
==Location and features== The falls are located in the [[Gold Coast hinterland]] district, near [[Springbrook, Queensland|Springbrook]].
At the base of the waterfall the moist conditions have created a good habitat for the [[Doryanthes palmeri|giant spear lily]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.epa.qld.gov.au/parks_and_forests/find_a_park_or_forest/springbrook_national_park/index.html |title=Springbrook National Park |accessdate=10 October 2009 |publisher=[[Queensland Government]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090910163455/http://www.epa.qld.gov.au/parks_and_forests/find_a_park_or_forest/springbrook_national_park/index.html |archivedate=10 September 2009 |df=dmy }}</ref>
