{{Use Indian English|date=January 2018}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}
[[File:Katary Falls (Kattery Falls) from Below.jpg|thumb|right|Katary Falls|200px]][[File:Kataryfall,selas,coonoor,india.jpg|thumb|Katery Falls in 2010]]
[[File:Places,around katery falls,coonoor.jpg|thumb|in and around Katery Falls]]
'''Katary Falls''' is  approximately 10 km from [[Coonoor]] in the [[Nilgiris district]] in the state of [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]. At 55 metres (180 ft) in height, Katary Falls is third largest waterfall in the Nilgiris; one can reach it by trecking.<ref name=a>{{cite web|url=http://www.visitindia.org.in/tamil%20nadu/coonoor.html|title=the Coonoor in Tamil Nadu |publisher=visitindia.org.in|accessdate=2011-09-21}}</ref>

The falls are the site of India's first hydel power plant, the [[Kateri hydroelectric system]].<ref name=a />

