[[File:Medvednica.jpg|thumb|Savica seen from the opposite bank of [[Sava]] river]]
'''Savica''' or '''Trnjanska Savica''' is a neighbourhood of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]], located on the left (northern) bank of [[Sava]] river, west of {{ill|Folnegovićevo naselje|hr|Folnegovićevo naselje (Folka)}} and east of Staro Trnje (Old Trnje). Part of the city district of [[Trnje]], the neighbourhood covers an area of {{convert|76.8|ha}} and, according to the [[2011 Census of Croatia|2011 census]], it is inhabited by 8,449 people.<ref>{{cite web|title=10. Mjesni odbor Trnjanska Savica|url=http://www.zagreb.hr/10-mjesni-odbor-trnjanska-savica/14213|website=Zagreb.hr|publisher=City of Zagreb|accessdate=25 May 2017|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stanovništvo Grada Zagreba po mjesnim odborima, Popis 2011.|url=http://www.zgizbori.hr/izbori/zgizborilokalni13.nsf/0/916FE48BF01BE3AEC1257B480051BB60/$FILE/Broj_stanovnika_po_gradskim_cetvrtima_i_mjesnim_odborima_Popis.pdf|website=Zgizbori.hr|accessdate=25 May 2017|language=hr}}</ref>
Savica was built according to the socialist model of a functional neighbourhood, which is planned to fulfill all day-to-day needs of its inhabitants. Construction of high-rise apartment buildings in Savica is still ongoing, mostly in the southeastern part of the neighbourhood.
The neighbourhood is served by the Jure Kaštelan Elementary School, Savica Farmer's Market, Savica Library and {{ill|State Geodetic Directorate of Croatia|hr|Državna geodetska uprava}}, and belongs to the Parish of blessed [[Aloysius Stepinac]].
==Gallery== <gallery class="center"> File:Stambeni neboder, Ulica Ljerke Šram 01.jpg|The largest apartment building in Savica, known colloquially as the "officer's skyscraper" File:Gradska tržnica Savica 02.jpg|Savica Farmer's Market File:Pogled na Savicu 01.jpg|Typical Savica architecture </gallery>
