{{Refimprove|date=September 2014}}
'''Zazamanc''' is the name of a [[legend]]ary African or Arabian [[country]] mentioned in [[Wolfram von Eschenbach]]'s [[epic poem]] ''[[Parzival]]''.<ref>{{cite book|last=Eschenbach|first=Wolfram von|title=Parzival|year=1980|publisher=Penguin}}</ref>  As a story embedded in Wolfram's poem, Zazamanc is generally seen as a myth created by Wolfram. However, Zazamanc is also mentioned in the [[Nibelungenlied]].

